# React Frontend Template

This template provides a standardized structure for creating new React applications in the Park Golf Platform.

## Application Structure

```
{app-name}/
├── src/
│   ├── app/
│   │   ├── App.tsx
│   │   ├── router.tsx
│   │   └── store/
│   ├── api/
│   │   ├── client.ts
│   │   └── {domain}Api.ts
│   ├── components/
│   │   ├── common/
│   │   │   ├── Layout/
│   │   │   ├── Button.tsx
│   │   │   ├── Input.tsx
│   │   │   └── Modal.tsx
│   │   └── {domain}/
│   ├── hooks/
│   ├── pages/
│   ├── contexts/
│   ├── types/
│   ├── utils/
│   ├── index.css
│   └── main.tsx
├── public/
├── package.json
├── tsconfig.json
├── vite.config.ts
├── tailwind.config.js
└── eslint.config.js
```

## Required Dependencies

- react
- react-dom
- react-router-dom
- @reduxjs/toolkit or recoil
- axios
- tailwindcss

## Environment Variables

- VITE_API_BASE_URL
- VITE_APP_NAME
- VITE_NODE_ENV

## Usage

1. Copy this template to create a new React application
2. Replace {app-name} and {domain} with actual names
3. Update package.json with application-specific information
4. Configure API endpoints in src/api/
5. Implement domain-specific components and pages